{"Title": "Confluence of graph rewriting with interfaces", "Year": 2017, "Source": "Lect. Notes Comput. Sci.", "Volume": "10201 LNCS", "Issue": null, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 141, "PageEnd": 169, "CitedBy": 6, "DOI": "10.1007/978-3-662-54434-1_6", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85018711620&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 Springer-Verlag GmbH Germany 2017.For terminating double-pushout (DPO) graph rewriting systems confluence is, in general, undecidable. We show that confluence is decidable for an extension of DPO rewriting to graphs with interfaces. This variant is important due to it being closely related to rewriting of string diagrams. We show that our result extends, under mild conditions, to decidability of confluence for terminating rewriting systems of string diagrams in symmetric monoidal categories.", "AuthorKeywords": ["Adhesive categories", "Confluence", "DPO rewriting systems", "PROPs", "String diagrams"], "IndexKeywords": ["Adhesive categories", "Confluence", "PROPs", "Rewriting systems", "String diagrams"], "DocumentType": "Book Series", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 2, "EID": "2-s2.0-85018711620", "SubjectAreas": [["Theoretical Computer Science", "MATH", "2614"], ["Computer Science (all)", "COMP", "1700"]], "AuthorData": {"23395957900": {"Name": "Bonchi F.", "AuthorID": "23395957900", "AffiliationID": "60005667, 60008134", "AffiliationName": "CNRS, ENS de Lyon"}, "22733984100": {"Name": "Gadducci F.", "AuthorID": "22733984100", "AffiliationID": "60028868", "AffiliationName": "University of Pisa"}, "33368106000": {"Name": "Kissinger A.", "AuthorID": "33368106000", "AffiliationID": "60016529", "AffiliationName": "Radboud University Nijmegen"}, "8406504300": {"Name": "Soboci\u0144ski P.", "AuthorID": "8406504300", "AffiliationID": "60025225", "AffiliationName": "University of Southampton"}, "6507161816": {"Name": "Zanasi F.", "AuthorID": "6507161816", "AffiliationID": "60022148", "AffiliationNam